            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> (if required!)</p><p>Combine the<strong> fig relish</strong> and <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>and whisk to combine – this is your <strong>figgy</strong> <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
